flowchart TD
    Client[Client 0 VRAM] --> Gateway[Managed Gateway / Router / State Store]

    subgraph ManagedInfra["Managed infra under our control"]
        Gateway
        Router[Latency / tier / oracle router]
        Store[Async Session State Capsule Store]
        OptionalDraft[Optional draft model]
        W4[Managed 14B/32B oracle]
    end

    Gateway --> Router
    Gateway --> Store
    Gateway --> OptionalDraft

    subgraph WorkerPool["P2P consumer GPU workers"]
        W1[Hot Worker 1.5B/7B]
        W2[Replacement Worker same tier]
        W3[Replica for race / queue relief]
    end

    Gateway -->|start session: prompt or latest checkpoint| W1
    W1 -->|accepted token chunks| Gateway
    W1 -->|async checkpoint every 50-100 tokens| Store
    W1 -->|hot state lives here during session| W1

    Store -.->|failover: latest capsule| W2
    Gateway -.->|reroute after failure| W2
    W2 -->|continue from capsule or prefill fallback| Gateway

    Gateway -.->|optional race on short requests| W3
    W3 -.->|first valid response may win| Gateway

    Router -->|hard prompts / async verify| W4
    W4 -->|oracle correction / rerank| Gateway

    Gateway --> Stream[Stream accepted tokens]
    Stream --> Client

    classDef client fill:#e8f5e9,stroke:#2e7d32,stroke-width:2px;
    classDef gateway fill:#e3f2fd,stroke:#1565c0,stroke-width:2px;
    classDef worker fill:#fff3e0,stroke:#ef6c00,stroke-width:2px;
    classDef oracle fill:#f3e5f5,stroke:#6a1b9a,stroke-width:2px;

    class Client,Stream client;
    class Gateway,Router,Store,OptionalDraft gateway;
    class W1,W2,W3 worker;
    class W4 oracle;
